description: A successful 10-year delay to removing part of the wall at L'Ancresse Bay passes the States.
title: Guernsey WW2 anti-tank wall removal delayed
title_page: Guernsey WW2 anti-tank wall removal delayed - BBC News
maintext: Deputy Al Brouard, who proposed the requete, said his main objection was to the installation of the groynes, which he claimed would prevent walking down part of the beach at anything but low tide.
